# React Router (BrowserRouter) handles client-side routing. Without this,
# direct GETs / bookmarks / shared links to client-side routes
# (/about, /interview-index, /rag-explore, etc.) return 404 from
# Netlify's edge before React ever loads.
#
# /retrieve and /.netlify/functions/* are still handled by the
# Function runtime — Netlify routes function paths before applying
# this catch-all.
